<p>I have the following 5 variables to check for a condition.</p>  <p><strong>Example</strong>:</p>  <pre><code>DECLARE @Col1 VARCHAR(10) = '' DECLARE @Col2 VARCHAR(10) = '' DECLARE @Col3 VARCHAR(10) = '' DECLARE @Col4 VARCHAR(10) = '' DECLARE @Col5 VARCHAR(10) = '' DECLARE @String VARCHAR(MAX)   IF @Col1 = '' AND @Col2 = '' AND @Col3 = '' AND @Col4 = '' AND @Col5 = '' BEGIN     SET @String = '' END ELSE IF @Col1 &lt;&gt; '' AND @Col2 = '' AND @Col3 = '' AND @Col4 = '' AND @Col5 = '' BEGIN     SET @String = '@Col1' END ELSE IF @Col1 = '' AND @Col2 &lt;&gt; '' AND @Col3 = '' AND @Col4 = '' AND @Col5 = '' BEGIN     SET @String = '@Col2' END ELSE IF @Col1 = '' AND @Col2 = '' AND @Col3 &lt;&gt; '' AND @Col4 = '' AND @Col5 = '' BEGIN     SET @String = '@Col3' END ELSE IF @Col1 = '' AND @Col2 = '' AND @Col3 = '' AND @Col4 &lt;&gt; '' AND @Col5 = '' BEGIN     SET @String = '@Col4' END ..... ..... ..... </code></pre>  <p>As the above conditions show, there are many probabilities.</p>  <p>How can I reduce the occurrences of multiple if conditions?</p>